# Frontend Rules — Client Layer

> Full contract: `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`

## Layer Import Policy (strict)
```
app → pages → features → shared
```

| You are in | You can import from | You CANNOT import from |
|------------|--------------------|-----------------------|
| `shared/` | (nothing) | features, pages, app |
| `features/` | shared | other features, pages, app |
| `pages/` | features, shared | other pages, app |
| `app/` | pages, features, shared | (no business logic) |

## Import Syntax
- **Always use `@/`** path alias. Example: `import { Foo } from '@/shared/components/Foo'`
- Never use relative paths with more than 1 level: forbidden `../../`
- Never use `../../../` or deeper

## TypeScript
- All NEW files: `.tsx` extension mandatory
- Never use `any`
- Existing `.jsx` files: do not migrate unless the current mission explicitly requires it

## Component Rules
- `app/`: only providers, router setup, global CSS imports. Zero JSX business logic.
- `pages/`: compose layouts + features for a route. No data fetching directly in page root.
- `features/`: self-contained domain slices. Each feature owns its own state, API calls, components.
- `shared/`: generic, reusable, domain-agnostic only.

## Style Rules
- Colors: Primary `#1B2A4A`, Accent `#39A900`, Background `#EEF0F5`, Surface `#FFFFFF`
- Never use `group`, `peer`, `has-[]` inside `@apply`
- Use Tailwind classes directly in JSX
- Prefer inline feedback. Toasts only for global network errors/success.

## Build Validation
```bash
pnpm -C client run build   # must exit 0
pnpm -C client run lint    # must exit 0
```
